== About François
François Gay-Balmaz is an Associate Professor in Mathematics at [https://www.ntu.edu.sg/ Nanyang Technological University (NTU)], Singapore, since September 2023. Previously he was a researcher at the [https://www.cnrs.fr/en Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique (CNRS, France)] at [https://www.ens.psl.eu/ Ecole Normale Supérieure de Paris (ENS)]. He received his Master (2004) and Ph.D. degrees (2009) from the [https://www.epfl.ch/en/ Swiss Federal Institute of Technology (EPFL, Switzerland)] and his Habilitation (2018) at [https://www.sorbonne-universite.fr/en Sorbonne University]. He was also a PostDoc at EPFL and at the [https://www.caltech.edu/ California Institute of Technology] (from 2009 to 2010).\n


== Current Research Interest

- *Structure-preserving discretization \& learning* \n
- *Variational principles in nonequilibrium thermodynamics* \n
- *Geophysical fluids* \n
- *Plasma physics* \n
- *Quantum-classical systems* \n



